{"key":"processedPost-11815278","value":{"id":11815278,"first":11815069,"last":11815278,"when":1263330536,"utime":"01/12/10 11:08 PM","content":"Probably.&nbsp; I've soaked that long before, but it's not recommended.&nbsp; Many endospores germinate and produce new endospores if allowed to soak too long.&nbsp; In addition, the bacteria consumes some of the sugars you want for your mycelium.&nbsp; Bottom line is it will probably work OK, but 12 to 24 hour soaks seem to be about optimum, especially if you rinse and begin the soak in hot tap water.<br />RR","title":"Re: Can I soak my grain for 48h ?","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}